  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This practice integrates reasoning about safety and reliability in the development process. The benefits are the&#xD;
    identification of the right set of requirements for a safety- and reliability-relevant system as well as the assessment&#xD;
    of the adequacy of architecture and design aspects meant to realize such requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The practice uses industry standard work products such as Fault Tree Analysis (FTA), Fault Means and Effect Analysis&#xD;
    (FMEA) and Fault Means, Effect, and Criticality Analysis (FMECA) and integrates the development of the work products&#xD;
    into the development process.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription>
